inn1.comm: right on the money, good length coupled with a probing line just outside off. Rohit is content not to play
fullish and quite straight as Rohit is made to come forward and defend
touch of swing away for Mills but it started a bit too wide outside off to trouble the batsman into playing
teasing length just outside off, but Rohit refuses to bite. The only ball he's played this over was the one that threatened to take out his middle stump
great, big shout from Mills. But that very full delivery on middle and angled down leg would have missed the stumps. Rohit went for an almighty heave over the top to no avail
shortish and angled into the body of Rohit who rises to his toes and drops it down with soft hands
fullish and a bit wide outside off and Kohli doesn't bother with it. Touch of outswing for him straight away
strides forward to meet this full length ball on and around off stump with a push to mid-off
length ball on middle and Kohli is easily behind it
more shape for Southee, and it was a nice, drivable length too. But he needs to be a bit straighter to make Kohli play.
goes wide on the crease and Kohli had to reach out to this one. Very full outside off stump and he taps it away just to the left of mid-off, who pulls out the dive and keeps it to one
ventures forward as this is full and shaping away from off stump. Nice-looking drive to mid-off to end the over
right up there on off stump as Kohli is on the front foot and whips a drive to mid-off.
length ball on middle as Kohli stays back and dabs it in front of midwicket. Nathan McCullum cannot prevent the quick single
lovely straight bat from Rohit again. It was a very full ball on off stump as well, with just a touch of away movement
goes forward and pokes his bat away from the body with an airy drive, didn't see this one dart back in at him, I think. Lucky to get an inside edge that runs off through square leg.
fullish and on and around off stump as Kohli plonks his front foot forward and blocks
chips down the track, while making sure he was making room outside leg. Mills shortens his length and Kohli adjusts as he steers the ball to point

both of these bowlers have been inviting the drive and there is one, not quite timed and it just had enough on it to sail over the head of mid-on. Hit the bat low and on the inside half as he looked to drive on the up through the off side
length ball down the pads, strikes it and goes through to the keeper.

oh, he's gone! Kohli's top-edged a short ball! It was the first one he faced today and he went for the pull. I wonder if his weight was more on the front foot than it should have been, but the ball seemed to come at him a little quicker and all he can do is given an relatively easy skier to Jimmy Neesham at midwicket
full and on off stump as he leans into a good drive through the extra cover area. Off the mark straight away
touch short and on the body as Rohit rides it off his hips behind square leg
fullish and around off stump again as he blocks off the front foot
fullish and around off stump as he comes forward to defend
inches forward to block the length ball on off stump
goes wide of the crease that time for the shorter ball on off stump. Rohit goes up on his toes and dabs it into the leg side
fuller length just outside off stump as he goes for an on-the-up drive to cover
shortish and just outside off stump as he rides it down behind point
another one rising around hip-height to Rohit as he works it away towards square leg, who was a little too quick for India to sneak a single

caught in no-man's land there. It was shortish and outside off stump and Rohit was stuck in the crease as he looked to put bat to ball. Looked very uncertain and it shows as the inside edge sneaks away to square leg
full and angled into his pads as Rahane nudges it to long leg and rotates strike. India need a lot of that right now
it's Rohit's turn to tuck it around the corner and scurry through for a quick single. Got forward to meet this full length ball on middle and leg
length ball angled in at him as Rahane doesn't need to do much, just flicks it off his pads to long leg off the back foot
short ball at 135 kph, good line too, right on top of middle. But Rohit's seen it early and sinks below it
bit more bounce than Rohit expected, but he somehow managed to keep the guide to third man go down and to the left of a diving gully
chops it to cover as this is shortish and just outside off

oh, it's in the air, it's gone way, way, way up and Baz races after it, sticks out his hands but it falls just outside his reach. It was a fullish length ball and Rohit went for a loft over the bowler's head and it went straight up
shortish and on and around off stump as he goes back and taps it towards the covers
fullish on middle and off as he comes forward to defend

charges him, that last loft did not faze Rohit and he goes through with the shot. Didn't get all of it but the short straight boundaries come to his aid. Got a little too under it and it hit a little higher on the bat than he would have liked, but he got the result
back of a length and it darts in off the pitch as Rohit chops into the covers
fullish on off stump as he pushes down the pitch. Mills' boot can't do the job and they sneak a single to mid-off

he's dropped it! Excellent delivery from Southee as he tests Rohit out in that channel just outside off. Pokes at it with very little footwork and a regulation outside edge goes just a touch low and to the left of Taylor who grasses it
back of a length and in that lovely off stump channel again as he opens the face a touch and guides it to point
punches to point off the back foot as Southee refuses to give him too much room
bouncer now, right on off stump as Rohit prefers to sway away
shortish and angled in on middle as Rohit tucks it away with soft hands towards midwicket and he scampers off
back of a length just outside off and Rahane pulls out the back foot defence from the coaching manual
back of a length and angled in on off stump. Rohit is off his feet and is quite cramped up but is able to sneak a single after pushing down towards mid-on

short delivery again and he's picked out long leg! Can't stop himself from going for the hook and he did not get on top of the bounce there. Gets a thick top edge that sails straight into the hands of Southee. Had to fetch that from a touch outside off
short again, this time Rayudu goes on the back foot and dabs it one-handed behind square leg for a single
back of a length and angled in on off stump as Rohit pushes from the crease with an opened face and finds point
full and seeking top of off, Rohit strides forward to block
fullish and wide outside off, Rohit is circumspect as he leaves it for the keeper
starts off with a back of a length delivery outside off, hustles through at 130 kph as Rayudu lets it go
136 kph, back of a length on and around off stump as he goes back and defends down the pitch
strays on the pads and Rayudu clips it away through square leg for a much needed boundary. Bit too full from Bennett and against wristy players, that is asking for trouble
139 kph, terrific! thuds into the pitch and it jags off the seam a log way. Rayudu has to suck in his gut as he trusts the bounce and lets it through
appreciable movement in at him again as Rayudu is beaten for pace. Didn't account for the indip there either as the ball clips the pads and runs away towards point
fullish and just outside off, leaves it well alone
131 kph, dug in on off stump and he was looking to play first, but then pushes his wrists down and lets the bouncer go through around nose-height to the keeper
well and truly on the back foot is Rayudu as he blocks this length ball outside off. Sucker ball outside off coming up?
opens the face as he runs this full one outside off to third man
back of a length just outside off stump. Could have flayed that over the covers, but at two wickets down, Rohit chooses to let it go
fullish and tailing down leg as he turns it towards midwicket off the front foot
short ball, moving in at him but with Mills' slightly lesser pace the batsman sees it early and drops his wrists
shortish and outside off stump, makes him hop up off his feet and blunt it down towards point
he has slammed that! Bennett's short ball rose only waist-high and Rohit is all to comfortable with that, pulling it off the front foot. Right off the middle!
gets this one to rise higher, and it's a bit more outside off as Rohit is up on his toes as he defends
changes it up with one full and on off stump as he comes forward to block well
fullish and angling down the leg side as he clips it away to deep square leg quite nicely
short ball but Rayudu is already camping on his back foot and he softens the grip and nudges the ball behind square leg for a quick single
fullish and just outside off, the perfect Test-match line, as Rayudu exhibits the front-foot leave
targets the middle stump with a fullish ball, draws the batsman forward to block
back of a length and he uses the bit of width on it to steer it towards the point region
touch wide again as Rayudu leans back and rolls his wrists on top of the ball as he guides it to point
nice short ball again, just outside off, as Rayudu jumps off his feet and dabs it with soft hands into the leg side. Very well controlled
generates good pace and height on this one too. Rohit sways away from the line of this bouncer outside off
keeps pushing him back as this was short and around off stump. Rayudu nudges it towards midwicket

bit of width and Rayudu looks to capitalise as he goes back and cuts but he cannot beat a very acrobatic Jesse Ryder. Leapt to his left and stuck a hand out to stop the ball that was rather well timed
loose delivery on the pads and Rayudu clips it off the back foot through midwicket with considerable ease. He should go back to bowling much shorter than that
and he does, and this one follows Rayudu too. Goes for the upper cut over third man but can't put bat to ball. Much better line of attack from the big fast bowler
another short one, but this time Rayudu steps back inside the line of it and pulls it down to long leg. That's very clever batting, knows it will be dug in and he was waiting for it
shuffles across to his off stump as he defends this shortish ball down the pitch.
full and straight and Rohit is able to come forward and tuck it through square leg
wide of the crease for a change in angle as this is pitched back of length and makes Rayudu guide it to gully with an open face
floated outside off but Rayudu cannot get his timing proper. Wen't forward enough and should have drilled that through the covers, but I guess it came a little slower off the pitch
very compact there as this was a good length ball outside off. Defended off the back foot
fullish and just outside off stump, Rayudu is wary of a little nibble of away swing as he lets it go
touch short outside off as he cuts it quite nicely to gully
and its short of a length on middle and leg as Rohit goes back and blocks it towards midwicket
length ball outside off, not bothered with
ventures straighter does Neesham and the batsman tucks it down to long leg for a single.
fullish on middle as he pushes down to mid-on off the front foot
quite full again and Rayudu's front foot movement isn't quite as pronounced as it should have been. Driven to mid-on again
this time he takes a couple of steps down the pitch, but the ball jags in off the pitch and does not afford any room. Just manages to keep it out and on that note, it will be drinks
its a bit short and pitched outside leg stump, and there is some turn as Rohit pushes it off to square leg
tossed up and it goes through the covers for a single as Rohit leans nicely forward
flighted on off as he defends off the front foot
holds it back a little and it allows Rayudu to clip it into the leg side for a single
full on middle and leg as he turns it towards midwicket
nudges it into the leg side but not far enough to evade the bowler
short ball, but it was straying down leg. Rayudu swivel pulls to square leg for a single. Didn't make good enough contact
leans right forward to block this full length ball on off stump.
advances down the track and goes for a mow over midwicket, but he gets a top-edge over the lone slip. One-bounce four down to third man
140kph, fullish on and around off stump as he blocks off the front foot
tucks him up and Rohit can only nudge this length ball towards midwicket
touch of shape in at the batsman at 137 kph as Rohit comes forward and meets it with a dead bat
flighted outside off as he comes forward and defends
nips down the track and drives the tossed up delivery on off stump to long-on. Neat stroke
touch of turn from middle as Rohit comes forward and turns it towards short fine leg
another trip down the track for Rayudu, but this time his nudge finds midwicket
quick little dart on off stump as he pushes it to the right of the bowler, but N Mac is too good off his own bowling
and there's more evidence of it, pushed towards long-on but Nathan pulls out a sliding stop
back of a length on middle and leg as Rohit moves inside the line and works it away to long leg
138kph, shortish on and around middle as Rayudu is a little cramped for room as he manages to block
fullish on off stump as Rayudu comes forward to defend. They're giving nothing away here.
charges him, but Neesham slips in the short ball. A very well directed one too as it forces the batsman duck under it, lest he loses his head
full and on the stumps as he clips it away to long leg
came on a bit slower than Rohit expected. He was almost down with his hook shot when the bouncer comes to him and hits the bottom edge and deflects onto his pads
there's some relief! Tossed up just outside off stump and Rayudu takes full toll of the room on offer. Swings with all his might and the ball just about makes it to the boundary rope on the full
another skip down the track and drilled to long-off. Flighted that one outside off again
pushed through quite full and across the right-hander who drives into the cover
violent slog meant to go over midwicket, but Rohit survives another edge! Too thick for the keeper to take it, too quick for him too
holds this back as Rohit looks to drive down the ground and it goes back uppishly to the bowler, Nathan dives for it but goes on the bounce
fullish and on the stumps as he nudges it towards midwicket
shortish and on the pads again as Rayudu shuffles across and works it to long leg to bring up the fifty partnership

there's a shot befitting Rohit's skill. It was a bit too full from Neesham and that was possibly the only thing wrong with the ball, there wasn't much room to work with but he opens the face on impact and beats mid-off
fullish and straying down the pads as he clips it away to backward square leg
looks to whip the short ball from outside off stump towards midwicket, but can't get on top of it well enough though he was well on his toes
shortish, around middle and leg as he works it into the square leg region and scurries through
one foot is off the ground as he swivels on this short ball and pulls it down to long leg for a single. Wonderfully controlled, looks like he's getting into rhythm
no spin that time, Rohit was looking for it as he set up for the whip through midwicket. Has to settle for a back foot push to the bowler
tossed up outside off stump as he leans into a drive through the covers
full and darted in on middle as he defends back to the bowler
another quick, flat delivery, though this time it could be because of Rayudu rushing down the track. Keeps him to a defensive push
drives uppishly and just past short mid-wicket as McCullum pegs away on an off stump line
tossed up on off as Rohit leans forward and pushes down the pitch
thick outside edge flies down to third man, it was never going to reach him but Devcich the substitute fielder rushes forward and gets his body in line to keep that to one
fullish and on and around off stump as he defends solidly
fifty and what a shot to get it! Hoists it straight down the ground after charging down the track. Right into a bunch of orange shirts, who all miss it.
fullish and targeting the stumps as he keeps it out
uses the pace of Neesham as this was short and had just enough room for him to ramp the ball over the keeper. Got it well fine of third man
this time the angled bat takes the back of a length ball down and to the right of gully
pushed through on middle as he tucks it away behind square leg
tossed up on off stump as he comes forward to block
fullish on middle and Rayudu presents a solid straight bat
touch of width and though he was stuck in the crease, he guides the ball into the covers
another slog that goes over the ropes, the good thing with that was he was hitting with the turn even if he hand't reached the pitch. Full swing of the bat to this length ball on leg stump
tossed up with a bit of room as he drives solidly, but straight to the man at cover
length ball on the pads as he clips it down to deep square leg. He's finding those singles a lot easier now
back of a length just outside off, Rayudu wants a single as he drops it at his feet with soft hands but Rohit was wary of the point fielder rushing in

short ball and guess what? And this rose nowhere near threatening enough. Rayudu's first movement was back and across and that made it all the more harder to pull this one comes just above waist-high. Gets a top-edge that settles safely in the keeper's gloves
fullish and outside off, draws Dhoni forward and opens the face and guides it down to third man
back of a length outside off, given safe passage to the keeper
flighted on the pads as he tucks it away towards vacant square leg
tossed up outside off as he pushes it into he covers. Lunged forward to reach the pitch
chips down the track as this is tossed up on middle and is driven down the ground
length delivery on middle as he stays in his crease and clips it towards square leg
tossed up outside off stump as Rohit leans into a lovely-looking drive down to long-off
tossed up on the pads as Dhoni goes forward and nudges it through midwicket
gets it through between point and cover as he got on top of the bounce. Short ball just outside off as he leaps off his feet to get the leverage needed to cut through the off side
shortish and this one is right on middle as Dhoni stays back and clips it to midwicket
back of a length outside off as he shuffles in line and pushes to mid-off
full and speared into middle as Dhoni, stuck in his crease, looks to whip it through the leg side but gets a thick outside leg to third man
full and speared down leg as Rohit leans forward and flicks it through square leg.
length ball but it comes on a little too quickly for Dhoni to connect well enough with the flick. Heavy ball, they say
nice and full outside off as Rohit strides forward and drives to long-off
chips down the track, but this one turns a touch. Dhoni wasn't accounting for that as he was playing outside the line and it takes his pad and goes to short fine
another chip down to meet this one on the pitch and drives to long-on
tossed up on middle and off as he drives back to the bowler
Rohit, you beauty! That is just caressed over the covers for a one-bounce four. Sheer timing as he leans forward and lofts the flighted ball over the in-field.
overcorrects this time as Rohit is able to nudge it away into the leg side for a single
length ball just outside off as he opens the face and runs it down to third man
he has cracked that, but he picked out the wrong fielder to hit to. Short and wide outside off and Dhoni cut it with all his might. But the ball was headed straight to Guptill in the covers
back of a length just outside off as he shuffles in line and pushes it mid-off
full on off stump as he prefers to drive from the crease and generates his power with a flick of the wrists. Mid-off pulls out a full-length dive to his right and saves some runs
bouncer, dug in a little too short as the Dhoni lets it through and lets the ump take over
back of a length on and around off stump as he shuffles across and clips it to deep midwicket
full face of the bat sends the ball rolling all along the ground to mid-on. Full length on middle stump from Bennett
but this one will take a bit of time, I think. Dhoni has launched it straight out of the ground! Magnificently muscled as he charges down the pitch first ball and slogs him over midwicket
darted on off stump as he makes some room and cuts into the covers. Dhoni's legs are quick enough to pick up a very quick single
this is tossed up outside off as he leans forward and drives to long-off
length ball outside off and Dhoni leaves this
touch short and just outside off as he goes back and makes some room, but cuts it straight to cover
tossed up on and around leg stump as he turns it towards midwicket.
shortish and a little outside off stump, Dhoni was lining that up too, but checks his shot as he pushes into the covers.
shortish and angled in at his body as Dhoni works it away behind square leg for a single
fullish on off stump and Rohit can't do much more than come forward and block. Took the bottom hand off and I think that bounced a little bit more than he expected
there's his fourth so far and he slaps it over extra again. Moves leg side and this was in the slot for it. Back of a length ball outside off sent packing as he stands up high and flat-bats it away
and that invites the bouncer over off stump and Rohit ducks out of the way
sees there is no slips in place and exploits that. Hint of room on this length ball and he dabs it to the right of the keeper for a very clever boundary
darted in on off stump as he pushes into the covers
holds the length back and cramps him on the leg stump as he picks him off through square leg

he's been caught down the leg side and Williamson strikes! He's had a few chances, but he's played some blistering shots in between and falls all too tamely. Length ball run almost off the face of the bat, but the keeper does well moving across to the leg side and parries it once before holding on. Quite safe from Ronchi
and he gets off the mark with a sublime stroke! Nicely tossed up outside off and he takes full toll. Leans forward and drives through the covers and the timing takes it all the way to the ropes
a bit too wide outside leg as he picks it off through square leg
touch too short as Dhoni goes back and cuts behind point and finds the third man boundary. Perfect placement and India's counterattack continues

saw a bit of width and he goes for a cut, but doesn't bother to keep it down and that is the end of him. Third man has to move to his left a bit and holds on to a reasonably easy catch and New Zealand take the edge as drinks come onto the field
fullish and angled across the left-hander, who is content to let it go to the keeper
full and just outside off again as this time Jadeja leans forward and pushes into the covers. He wants the single but Dhoni waits for the ball to go past the diving Neesham, but it doesn't. No single
short ball, rising above shoulder height on leg stump as he leaps off his feet and defends down by his legs
back of a length outside off, left alone
pursues the channel outside off again and Jadeja does not try that ugly waft he sometimes can't help himself with. Good on him
short ball on leg stump but Dhoni, though he did rock back, and just nudges it towards deep square leg
slowed it up and targets middle as Jadeja gets an inside edge onto pad
tossed up on middle and off as he draws Jadeja forward and into a defensive push
drifts down the pads and he clips it to long leg quite neatly for a couple that gets him off the mark
excellent line to the left-hander, and he gets a little bit of turn too. Jadeja defends off the front  foot and gets a thick outside edge
leans right forward to get to the pitch and nudges it down the ground. N Mac dives to his left and gets a hand to it. The batsman think about running on the misfield, but Jaddu sends his captain back
back of a length outside off as Dhoni lets it go
seemed to lose his balance after he shuffled across and whipped it off his hips to long leg. Plonks his bat down into the pitch to steady himself and picks up the run

the bowler wanted to outsmart the batsman but has to end up paying for it. Jaddu makes some room and advances but Southee pushes it well wide outside off. Umpire calls him on it, but it might have been a harsh one
length ball on the leg stump as he tucks it away to deep square leg
back of a length outside off and Dhoni doesn't bother with this either
touch fuller, but it is still a little too wide to interest Dhoni
dabs it to point as this is back of a length outside off
tossed up on off stump as Jaddu comes forward to block
flighted on middle and leg as he reaches forward and drives down to long-on
right up there in the block hole as Dhoni pushes it to long-on from the crease
gives it a little air while keeping the line nice and tight on the stumps. Jadeja pushes down the ground for a single
touch short on the pads as he picks him off his hips to long leg
flighted on middle as Jaddu reaches forward and whips it to midwicket
back of a length outside off as Dhoni can only chop it down to mid-on with a horizontal bat
full on middle and leg as Dhoni clips it from the crease towards midwicket
short ball just outside leg stump and Jaddu goes back to hook and gets enough bat, actually it was a top edge, on it to get it fine and help himself to a four to long leg. Didn't look in full control
fullish on middle but Jadeja is behind it
short again, but this hook is played better. Took it from outside off stump and rolled his wrists down on it to find deep square leg

even Guptill can't stop that as Dhoni goes for a slap through the covers. Originally it looked like he'd gotten hold of that, but the ball seems to slow down as it neared the boundary. Too short and too wide from Southee
tossed up on middle and off as he gets forward to defend
works it away to deep square leg as he lunged forward to clip it to deep square leg
tossed up on leg stump as Dhoni is contend blocking it to the right of the bowler
flighted on leg as he goes forward and turns to midwicket
little chip down the track as he presents a straight bat and finds long-on
excellent line on off stump as he forces Jaddu to defend
back of a length outside off as Dhoni is deep in his crease and cuts into the covers
keeps at that line just outside off stump and Dhoni prefers to play off the back foot and he flick-drives into the covers
fullish on off stump as Dhoni stays on the back foot. Dhoni's hands are too good on that occasion as he manages to push it to mid-off
that time he comes forward and runs with the stride as he drives to mid-off. The fielder had to move to his left a bit and Dhoni hadn't hit it too hard
magnificent shot! It was short and wide and needed to be put away and Jaddu is looking in top form as he goes back and slaps it through point. No stopping that
back of a length, but the line is more tighter outside off as he opens the face and guides it to point
tossed up on middle as he punches it back to the bowler
friendly full toss on off stump as Dhoni looks to hit it a little too hard and doesn't time it or place it. Straight to midwicket
tossed up outside off as he drives all along the ground to long-off
length on and around off stump he he dabs it through towards point
full and angled into the pads as he goes down on one knee and slog-sweeps him flat over midwicket. Lots of power from the bottom hand there
tossed up on middle as he comes forward and keeps it out
starts off with a short ball, but he doesn't get it to rise high enough. Dhoni was camped on the back foot and slams it wide of mid-on. Punishing stroke from the India captain
stays well inside the line of this one as he cuts the length ball outside off to third man. More of a thickish outside edge than anything

Jaddu follows suit! This one rose a little higher and it was outside off stump too, but he has no hassles in pulling that well in front of square! Authoritative strike on a relatively slower pitch than Eden Park
fuller and angled across the left-hander, who leans forward and opens the face to guide it to point
fullish on off stump as he pushes down to mid-off with a straight bat

he's launched that over mid-off's head! 200 up for India as Jaddu cuts loose. Another one that doesn't go too high off the ground, but it was struck so wonderfully well that it clears the ropes. It was begging for the shot though as Bennett overpitches outside off
back of a length on the pads as Dhoni jumps off his feet to keep the ball down
shortish on off stump as he goes deep in his crease and nudges it through midwicket. Calls for two and Jaddu responds handsomely. Easily done as the fifty partnership comes up
moves across to off stump as he guides this just in front of point to pick up a single as Mills pushes the back of a length ball across him
slower ball at 116 kph as he gets the offcutter just outside off stump. Jaddu stays back to negotiate the shorter length and guides to point
another slower ball as Jaddu sees it and dabs it, from the crease, towards point for a single
full and on the pads as he flicks it away to deep square leg for a single
short and wide outside off stump as Dhoni drags it towards midwicket with a one-legged pull
the opportunity was there and Jaddu takes it. Shorish ball outside off stump and he gets it fine of the short third man with a little late cut
slower, length ball on middle as he turns it away dead square on the leg side
yorker on middle and leg as he digs it out to long-on
short ball outside off as he gets up on his toes and rides it towards point
length ball on and around the stumps as Dhoni shuffles across and nudges it to the man at 45 degrees for a quick single
chips down the track and nudges it square of the short fine leg as this was on a length and on the pads as Mills continues around the wicket

full toss on leg stump and it's picked away past short fine leg. Asking for trouble with this field and he gets it. I might be tempted to agree he really has got super powers, especially in the area of making bowlers bowl poor balls
full on middle and leg as he clips it to midwicket quite solidly
slower ball, on a length and just outside off as he dabs it square into the off side
back of a length slower ball as he dabs it to short third man, good delivery that from Mills

another very silly ball from Mills and he knows it. It was short, it was slow and all Jaddu had to do was swivel around and pull it past short fine. The fielder should really have stopped that, but he dives over it!

he was looking to clean up the bowler there! Neesh, thank your lucky stars you were quick enough to duck underneath that absolute rocket from one of the hardest hitters of the cricket ball! Short, with a bit of room outside off and he flat-bats it murderously down the ground for his fifty
another short ball, but this one rises considerably higher to ruin his timing. Gets a top edge towards midwicket and picks up a single
slower ball from around the wicket, but his radar slips as it goes down leg and is called on it
shortish and outside off this time as he changes his pace. Jaddu can only guide it to point this time
120 kph offcutter again as Jaddu stays back and cuts it to deep point for only a single
goes back and a little to the leg side as he works this short ball outside off through to deep point with an open face
full and just outside off as he punches it down the ground, but Neesham gets down on his follow through
charges down the track and flays the full ball on leg stump to long-on as Mills continues around the wicket.
back over to the left-hander as this is full and outside off. Driven to long-off quite strongly
clips it straight to short fine leg as this is length on leg stump. Lucky for Mills
low full toss outside off stump as he plonks his front foot forward and drives to long-off
back of a length and pushed across him. Dhoni looks to flick-drive it through the covers, but just can't connect. Lots of wrist in that shot
back of a length on and around off stump as he goes deep in his crease and runs it to deep third man. Good over for NZ, only five off it

digs it in shortish and the ball doesn't bounce as high as the batsman thought. Goes for the pull and he wanted to smoke it, but the ball sneaks under his bat and his middle stump was in considerable danger there
swings off his hips and gets the benefit of a top-edge which flies away over the keeper's head. Hint of width for Dhoni to take advantage of and though it didn't go where he wanted, he'll he content
slower ball as it goes down the leg side and the keeper misses it too. Dribbles through his legs and they sneak a single along with the wide
another wide, as he looks for the full yorker outside off. Jaddu tries to reach, but then pulls away

consecutive fifties for Jaddu as he raises his bat and punches the air in triumph. Gets hold of this full toss outside off stump and chops it through the covers and finds the gap. Just concentrated on doing that, didn't hit the ball too hard
this time he gets the wide yorker right. Jaddu looks to get a little bat on it to third man, but misses

N Mac, you beauty! The bowler let himself down with another full toss outside off and this time Jaddu placed his front foot outside leg stump and drilled it down the ground. Long-off rushes across and dives full length to save two.
nope, isn't as lucky second time around. Full toss outside off again, only difference was Jaddu slapped this way more harder
full and down the leg side as he gets forward and swings the length ball past short fine leg, but Ross Taylor at deep backward square mops up
moves outside leg as he caresses this low full toss through towards the cover fielder
short ball, absolutely no danger as this doesn't even rise to waist high. Ample time to get under it and slap it over cow-corner off the back foot
full and pushed across him as Dhoni moves outside off stump and looks to be a bit too cheeky. Looks to scoop it over dine leg and ends up missing the ball
charges down the track and ensures he has a bit of room to work with, but Mills bowls it wide outside off and limits Dhoni to a single as he chops his bat down on it and hits through the covers
outstanding slower ball at 100 kph as Jaddu was looking to line this up, but the length was too full and it had absolutely no room on it. Has to settle for a guide into the covers with an open face
length ball well wide of off stump as he stays back and drags this one through midwicket for a single
whack! Don't bowl length to me, Dhoni  seemed to say with this shot. Got forward and slammed it over wide-long on. Came off the toe, but it is Dhoni after all
short ball as he goes back and pulls strongly. Goes on the bounce to deep square leg

there should not have been any runs there at all but India pick up two! Fuller length ball down the leg side and it clips the pad on the way to the keeper. Dhoni was rushing across to the other and and Jaddu responded so late. The keeper underarms it to the bowler and Jaddu was almost resigned to being run out when Neesh misses the stumps at the bowler's end. He could have waked over to it and clipped the bails off, but the underarm throw misses
full and on the pads again as Jaddu looks to tickle away fine, but can't get bat to it

he has crunched it and it clears the banks again, that's the second time he has put the ball in the trees beyond the midwicket boundary. It was a scrambled-seam length ball and Dhoni saw it early and smacks it away. What a finish by the India captain!

inn2.comm: back of a length with a little bit of room as Guptill cuts to the left of over. Timed it pretty well, but a very acrobatic leap from Rayudu keeps it to none
but Aaron cannot back it up. Got the toe end as he went for the cut again and the ball scurries down to third man who lets it through between his legs
back of a length, but a lot more straighter this time as Guptill stands up tall and defends
bit of room again and Guptill cuts straight to point. He's already playing a lot more shots early today
a bit too full to cut, but that is what Guptill does and benefits with an inside edge that goes to the left of the keeper and runs off to the fine leg boundary
good length and tighter on off stump as Guptill still prefers to play off the back foot. Solidly defended this time around
and he generates some movement across the left-hander. Excellent length and line on that off stump corridor and the seam away beats Ryder as he looked to poke from the crease
another boundary through third man as he throws his bat at a fullish, but slightly wider delivery.  Gets a thick outside edge as his feet move very little again
fullish and on off stump as he defends from the crease and moves his front foot after the fact

shortish and a little too leg-sidish as Ryder tucks him down to long leg, who is rather wide and has a lot of work to do. Bhuvi does his best as he pulls out a sliding tackle to kick the ball inside the field of play, but can't do it
on the other side of long leg this time. Too straight again from Shami and he moves back easily enough and clips it off the pads to the square leg boundary. Lovely timing from Ryder
139 kph, responds with a quick bouncer which rises around head-height. Ryder was shaping to hook, but decides against it
murdered through point! Bhuvi's given him way too much room and Guptill tucks into it with supreme authority. Cuts it off the front foot
oh, beauty! That's more like it, ventures fuller and keeps it tight on a fourth-stump line. It hits the seam and moves away as Guptill is beaten all ends up
fullish and just outside off again, this time Guptill is more circumspect as he leaves it
goes back despite the ball being on the fuller side, but he is right behind this one outside off stump. Much better line from Bhuvi
lovely line as this is full and just outside off, left alone off the front foot
right up there on off stump as Guptill jams his bat down on off stump and finds short cover
keeps it just outside off as this is on a length, but Ryder is camped on the back foot as he punches through the covers, but hasn't timed it well enough, for a quick single.
full and speared in at the pads as it hits the front one and rolls through to Dhoni
fullish and on middle and leg as Guptill nudges it between midwicket and mid-on for a single as the fielders stand right on the edge of the circle
length ball on the pads as Ryder clips it to deep backward square leg, who had just gone back. Short fine had come in for that ball
back of a length and it was right on middle too, Guptill tries to find the gap straight of midwicket, but can't
touch too wide and Guptill's been generous with the cut so far in this little innings. Finds deep third man and retains strike

shapes away just a bit, but the length was a little shortish and had a bit of width on it too. Guptill chops it to backward point, who misfields a bit to leak a single. India should be panicking about that aspect of play though
back of a length on off stump as Ryder gets back and defends solidly
good length, pushed across him as Ryder ventures forward and guides it to point
lovely straight bat from Ryder as his front foot movement gets better. Full length ball from Bhuvi on off stump. Good, tight cricket
too good that time, magnificent timing from Ryder as he gets forward and drives on the up and to the right of Binny at short cover. Had no chance and the outfield takes care of the rest
back of a length outside off as he stays in his crease and guides to point
full and straying on the pads as Guptill is able to beat midwicket, but he hasn't timed it well enough to go to the boundary
shortish but not as wide as Guptill thought as he went for the cut and gets a thick edge to point

one-bounce four, but the authority on that stroke was unquestionable. Guptill is looking for his shots here as this was dug in. He was quick to pull it and though it was off the toe of the bat, but his power is too good
another one and this is even better! Stands up tall and slaps it through point as Shami strays short and wide.
back of a length just outside off as he punches it down to mid-off
fullish just outside off stump as he defends to mid-off. Giant stride forward
fullish and on middle and leg as Ryder pushes forward and finds mid-on
nice and tight on middle and off is Bhuvi as he keeps the batsman to a back foot defensive to short cover
neat little clip to deep square leg as this was a little fuller on middle. Lots of wristwork in that shot and his balance was impeccable
fullish on leg stump as Guptill moves forward and drives to mid-on
inside edge and it goes just wide of Dhoni, who was moving outside off to collect the ball and was wrong-footed.

fullish ball on leg stump and Guptill has launched that over wide-long on for the first maximum of the innings. And it brings up the New Zealand fifty too. Motoring along are these two and their timing is something to behold!
goes down with this wide almost-yorker length ball as he looks to find the gap between mid-off and cover, but he can't get good enough bat on it

oops, Ryder's wasted another start as he drags onto his leg stump. He was camped on the back foot even as this was a little fuller and just outside off. Went for that thump through extra cover again, but only manages an inside edge that has every chance to go between the huge gap between bat and pad and knock him over

magnificent. both by Williamson and Rahane at point. It was shortish and just outside off as he stands up on his toes and punches square through the off side and point dives and pulls off a stunning save
fullish and on off stump as he goes forward to block

how is that for elegance? Poor ball though, half-volley on leg stump but Williamson was in perfect position to clip it straight of midwicket and his timing is good enough to beat two men chasing after the ball. No dive
this time he finds midwicket as Aaron goes a touch shorter and keeps it on middle. That time the fielder was desperate enough to dive to his left

changes of ends does the trick for Shami! Guptill was caught in the crease as this one keeps a touch low. Was looking for the clip through the leg side and is struck on the pads just on the knee-roll. Guptill knows it's gone as he gives a small nod and walks off
136kph, he's too good at point, is Rahane! Touch of width outside off as he goes back and cuts to point, but the man dives to his left and gets two hands to it
138 kph, it was the incutter this time. Length ball just outside off stump as he is rooted to the crease and looks to defend, but was playing all over the shot. Cut him in half
short of a length as it comes back in at him. Taylor was back and he turns it around to fine leg for a single
fullish on off stump as Williamson goes forward to block
back of a length on and around off stump as he is behind it
140 kph, full and on middle as Taylor presses forward and drives to mid-on with a consciously straight bat
139kph, bit too short and wide and Taylor capitalises as he moves just a bit back and across to the off side and cuts between point and cover
143kph, shortish and a little closer to off stump as this nips back, but Taylor chops it down to deep third man with rather effortlessly
143 kph, back of a length on the same line as Taylor cut to third man, but Williamson stands up and pushes it back down the pitch
too quick on the shot as this was still at 143 kph. Went for the cover drive on the up as he sees a bit of width on this fullish delivery, but gets a thick inside edge to mid-on
143kph, that time he waits for the shortish ball outside off to come to him and runs it down to third man with the open face
turn and bounce too! Gripped the surface and Williamson's cut shot is completely beaten!
gives it a bit more air as he draws Williamson forward, but the result is the same as he gets big turn outside off
fullish on off stump as he ventures forward and defends, far less solidly
tossed up outside off as he defends to point
touch shorter as Williamson goes deep in his crease and opens the bat to find point
ends the over with a peach, just like he started, as Williamson goes back to punch through the covers and is beaten comfortably. Loads of turn and bounce for the left-armer
full on off stump as Taylor leans right forward to get to the pitch and drive to long-on
bit of drift outside off as he tossed it up and gets a hint of turn. Williamson leaves it easily
on a length as he rides the turn to clip behind square leg for a single
held it back a little as Taylor drives a little uppishly down the ground
chips down the track and pushes the flighted ball outside off back to the bowler
flighted outside off as he drives to long-on rather comfortably. Difference between the ball spinning away and spinning in, I suppose
touch shorter on off stump as he punches into the covers
tossed up and angled in at him, but Williamson waits for it to turn and defends off the back foot
length ball, outside off and Williamson is content to let it go
flighted outside off as he draws Willliamson into a push through the covers off the front foot
darted this in on middle and leg as Taylor went back in front of all three stumps and defends
pushed through just outside off as he goes back and taps it through point
tossed up on leg stump and this was the one that goes the other way. Taylor didn't pick it as he looked to drive through the on side and gets a leading edge to mid-off
flighted on the pads again as he nudges it towards square leg
tossed up on middle as Williamson comes forward and clips confidently to midwicket
holds the length back and that allows Williamson to work the ball square of midwicket
carrom again, but this time Taylor is wary as he drives towards mid-off, but Ashwin runs and dives to get a hand to it
offspinner this time, on a length outside off as Taylor goes back and taps it back down the ground after letting it turn
tossed up outside off as Williamson strides forward and drives down to long-off solidly
darts it in on off stump and Taylor goes back. Might have kept a little low, but he gets his bat down just in time
only the smallest hint of room and that is enough for Taylor, beats the man at a widish gully with the late cut
flat on off stump and it turns a touch too. Goes back and pushes the ball into the off side
flat and just outside off again as Taylor stays on the back foot and punches through the covers
darted on off stump as Williamson goes back and finds cover
keeps it tight on middle as Taylor goes back and pushes it down the ground. Can't beat Ashwin
again, no room to work with as he has to punch down the ground
tossed up and he gets a little turn, which Taylor uses as he moves forward and nudges it behind square leg
just short enough for Williamson to go back and work it off his pads to long leg
tossed up on off stump as the batsman comes forward to defend
slower through the air this time, but Taylor is quick on the back foot as he cuts the length ball to backward point
tossed up outside off stump and Taylor is happy to leave it
right up there on middle as Taylor comes forward and drive to long-off
that was a ripper. Drifts in to pitch on middle and off and it grips and turns right across the front-foot defence of Williamson. Dhoni whips off the bails in a flash
loops it outside off stump as Williamson reaches out and drives uppishly through the covers
drops it a little short and Taylor moves back to chop the ball towards point
fullish and darted in on off stump but Taylor looks to late cut again! Very dangerous shot and that could have cannoned into the stumps, but he gets good bat on it and finds wide gully
chips down and hits it in the air between the two men at midwicket and widish mid-on. Has he placed that perfectly or was that just lucky?
tossed up on middle as he nudges towards midwicket
wasn't the offspinner this time as Taylor comes forward and blocks
loud shout for leg before as this turns appreciably away from the right-hander. Carrom ball from Ashwin strikes him on the back pad, but the spin was too much, I suspect
comes forward and pushes to cover point, calls for a single, but it is not there
pushed down towards mid-on but he nudges down the pitch, but can't beat Ashwin again
tossed up outside off and Willliamson is drawn into reaching out and driving on the up. Turn beats the shot and Dhoni whips off the bails
gives it a lot of air outside off as Williamson defends
tossed up outside off as he drives to point
flighted on off stump as he reaches forward and finds long-off
driven to long-off as this is full on off stump.
drops the length short as Williamson moves back and pushes to deep cover with a straight blade and a high elbow
flighted on leg stump as he leans forward and turns it past the backward square leg fielder
fullish on leg stump and it was the carrom ball again. Got right forward and drives to long-on with a straight bat
waits for it to turn off a length from off stump and picks it away to long leg
tossed up on off stump and it turns the other way again, reaches right forward to defend
another carrom ball from Ashwin as Taylor strides forward and adjusts at the last minute
that one goes awry as Taylor shuffles across to the off side a bit and glances it very fine to pick up a useful little boundary to signal drinks
fullish and nibbling away just outside off stump. Williamson goes for a back-foot punch, but misses
length ball on off stump as he runs it down to third man with an open face.
stays on the back foot as this is short of a good length and is defend
length ball on middle as he nudges to midwicket
just short of a good length outside off as he goes for a cut and misses it
a bit more room on offer as he goes back and cuts it to deep third man
starts off nicely as this is length on middle and Taylor defends
offcutter and it leaps off the pitch to take the glove as Taylor went back and punch into the covers
back of a length down the leg side as he clips it to deep backward square leg, who sends in a wild through that goes over the keeper and to point
fullish on and around middle and off as Taylor clips it wide of midwicket
full on middle as Williamson leans forward and clips it past the man at midwicket again
half-volley on off stump and that brings a bit of release for New Zealand as Taylor beats a packed offside infield and finds the cover boundary. Crisp cover drive off the front foot
shortish and a little wide of off stump, Williamson was right in going for the cut, but he just can't connect. Dhoni's brilliant standing up
fullish on middle and off as he drives down down the ground to mid-on as the umpire hands out the first warning for Bhuvi for running down the pitch
you beauty! Length ball on off stump and he just picks it up and lofts it over mid-on and has timed it so well that he clears the ropes. Fifty partnership brought up in style
opens the face to steer this length ball on off away to deep point
shortish and a little wide of off stump as Taylor chops it behind to third man again
charges down the track as Dhoni had slipped back to his normal position behind the wicket. Goes for an almighty heave over the off side but only connects with a whole lot of air
tossed up on off stump as he nudges it towards midwicket
flighted on middle and off as he clips it into the on side again
gives him some room and Taylor moves across to the off side and plonks a big front-foot stride as he punishes this through the covers
tossed up on middle and off as he comes forward and drives to long-on
doesn't turn it much, does Rayudu as he keeps this on a good length just outside off. Willliamson dabs it to short third man
tossed up outside off as he rushes forward and almost yorks himself. Digs it out to long-on as he beats a diving Rayudu

edged over point and Williamson slips at the non-strikers' to keep it to a single. It was full and just outside off and perhaps there might have been a bit of away shape to defeat his loft over mid-on
full on the off stump as he leans forward and defends solidly
cuts to deep third man, who does well to keep it to a single. Bit of width outside off and he gets it off the outside half of the bat and went in the air, but wide of point
139 kph, short ball right over off stump makes Williamson sway away from the line and drop his wrists
another one, this at 142 kph and Williamson evades it again. Head-high bouncer, well bowled and well played
makes room outside leg as he looks to flat bat it over mid-off and just about does it. Didn't get proper hold as this short ball on off stump bounced a little more than he expected
length ball on off stump as he goes back and punches towards mid-on
slower and with a bit of room outside off as Taylor goes back and late cuts it down to third man

chips down the track and flicks the ball in the air towards the region of a very straight midwicket. Virat Kohli is there and he leaps to his left, gets one hand to it but can't hold on. Could that be called a drop?  Probably not
length ball outside off stump as he cuts it away to deep third man
chips down the track and having reached the pitch he drives to long-off
reaches as far  forward as he could having seen this one nicely tossed up outside off. Drills a drive into the covers
gets it off the toe as he sets up for a pull. This was short and wide outside off so he had the room for the shot but, without any timing on the ball, finds midwicket
dug in at 143 kph and this was on middle too but Williamson rocks back and pulls through the vacant square leg, who is in the deep instead and keeps it to a single
140 kph, he's been very good on the cut all day today. And Aaron offers width as well. No need to ask twice as he beats the man in the deep comfortably
141kph, he's quick but he's wasting it. Short and wide again and Taylor this time doesn't even bother keeping it down. Hits it well to the left of him and collects another boundary
140 kph, bangs it in short again and this is way too high outside off stump. Taylor leaves it and collects an easy wide
143 kph and Taylor knows that was good. This was short, but it was closer to off stump and Taylor goes for the cut again but is comfortably beaten
142 kph, back of a length on off stump as he shuffles across and blocks
full on middle as he nudges it to a straightish midwicket
that's magnificent from Williamson, we've seen that before. Charges down the track and opens up his stance to slap the flighted ball over cover. And he's got more than enough bat on it
shortish on middle and leg as he goes down on one knee and pulls to the deep midwicket
shortish and outside off as he punches down the ground into the off side to bring up the single that takes him to a very calm, composed fifty
chips down the track as he makes a little room and hits the flighted ball in the air to long-off
absolutely gorgeous. It was short and had the smallest bit of room and Taylor goes deep in his crease and cuts the ball so very late. Short third man chases after it but he had no chance
shortish and outside off stump as he punches into the covers off the back foot
short ball on middle and off as he rocks back and pulls in front of deep backward square leg, who runs around but by the time he gets the throw in the batsmen have taken two
uses the pace as this is is short and outside off stump, stays back in his crease and runs it to deep third man
138 kph, fullish on middle and leg as Williamson covers his stumps and nudges it midwicket
back of a length just outside off as Williamson punches this 137 kph back of a length ball to point, where Rahane has been impenetrable
No matter, he'll go over Rahane. Shortish and had a bit of room as Williamson is on his back foot and lofts the ball over point's head. Pushed his whole body into that stroke to get his power
tossed up on off stump as he drives down to long-on
length ball on middle and leg as Williamson goes back and turns it past backward square leg to bring up his fourth fifty of the series
flighted on off stump as he drives down to long-off. Even against Ashwin these two are finding it so easy
it's a no-ball! Ashwin's overstepped as this one was a length ball that turns away and is defended
tossed it up as Williamson charges him and yorks himself. Doesn't connect and it sneaks through Dhoni's feet for a bye

this is short and wide outside off as Taylor rocks back and cuts him behind point. Dhoni is not at all mused by that as he goes down to have a talk with his bowler even as the ball goes off to the boundary
tossed up on middle and leg as he drives to mid-on
fullish and it turns from off stump as Williamson opens the face and drives to the covers
tossed up on off stump as he comes forward and blocks, head over the ball
tossed up on leg as Williamson comes forward and nudges to deep midwicket
flighted on off as he comes forward and drives to long-off. They're milking this nicely
tossed up and it is slower through the air and that makes the batsman reach out as he drives through the covers
pushed through on middle and leg, but it turns as Taylor moves back and defends in front of all three stumps
length ball on off stump as he punches down the ground and past a diving Ashwin
slower and tossed up again as this turns to take the inside edge and wander off towards midwicket
fullish and outside off, and this turns the other way, as Taylor reads it off the pitch and blocks
pushed through down the leg side as he looks to whip to fine leg, but can't connect
holds the length back as the batsman punches down the ground to mid-on
flighted on off stump and he beats man inside the circle in the covers as he opens the face
shortish on middle and leg as he works it off his hips through square leg
tossed up on middle and leg as he moves outside the line of it and drives to long-off
flighted on and around off stump as he drives with an open face and beats the short cover fielder who rushes to his left
just a touch short and Taylor rocks back and cuts it to the third man boundary. When you give this guy room, better brace yourself
flighted just outside off as he stays on the back foot and rides the turn with an open face to point
length ball on leg as he pushes past midwicket
tossed up on and around off stump as he goes forward and drives to long-ff
tossed up on off as he plonks his front foot forward and drives, but short midwicket is in the way
touch too short as Taylor stays back and cuts to backwards point
leg slip was in place, but Williamson went back and picks it off his hips past him. Mohammed Shami runs to his right and dives to keep it to two
length ball which turns down the leg side as he clips it away to square leg
tossed up on middle and leg as he leans forward and drives through midwicket
fullish on off stump as Taylor comes forward and blocks to the bowler
length just outside off as he rocks back and looks to cut, but can't connect

direct hit and he's gone! Williamson has to walk back and Jaddu has done it! It was on the pads and he went forward and nudges it towards short mid-on and set off, but Jaddu rushes to it grabs hold with the right hand, slips it into his left, swivels around to take aim at the non-strikers' and his dead-eye throw finds Williamson well short
tossed up outside off as he drives back to the bowler
flighted on off stump again as this gets a little turn and gets a thick outside edge
give it some air as he he reaches forward and defends
flighted on off and the batsman can do no more than defend
tosses it up nicely and this is a little slower too. Baz reaches right forward and plays outside the line as he is struck on the pads. Wild appeal, but impact was umpire's call outside off
clipped towards midwicket as he pinches a single
flighted and clipped away to straightish midwicket
goes back as he turns it off his pads to the leg slip fielder as the ball falls just short.
carrom ball and it bounces a bit more as Taylor is struck on the glove as he came forward to defend

oh dear, Dhoni was shouting "easy, easy" but the fielder wanted to go for the throw. It was nudged softly into the midwicket region and Baz called his partner through. Underarms it in but it goes well wide of the keeper and even past point for overthrows
shortish and just a touch outside off as he goes back and cuts to point
fullish on off stump at 131 kph as he defends off the front foot
touch short allows Taylor to go back and pull to long-on. Not enough width for that shot, but he knew that and adjusted a bit
125 kph, slower ball defeats Baz as he strides forward and looks to drive on the up through the covers. Gets a thick inside edge to midwicket instead

hit right back at Shami and he sticks his left hand up and out over his head, but he drops it. Very tough chance as it was hit quite hard and he wrings his fingers. Would that be a turning point? And would that have carried to Jaddu at mid-off had it not been deflected off his hand? No, that would be asking for a little too much
shortish and there was just about enough room for Taylor to time his cut, but Rahane is too good at backward point. Dives to his left and saves a few runs and that's drinks
tossed up on leg as he nudges down to mid-on
full on off stump as Taylor comes forward to defend
flighted on off stump as he looks to clip it through midiwcket, but gets a leading edge. Ashwin dives to his left to stop it from going off down the ground, but he can't reach
flighted on off as he reaches forward to defend
big front foot stride as he opens the face and defends with bat close to pad
finishes off with a flighted on on middle which he keeps out with a big stride forward. One off that over
124kph, offcutter with width on offer and Taylor cashes in. Reaches forward and ensures he has enough room to for a full swing of the arms. Demolished through the covers

fullish on middle and off as he defends with soft hands and runs through for a very tight single. Just about quick enough as the short midwicket fielder, Rayudu, gets to the ball but can't throw down the stumps. Might have reached even if he had. Gee, Taylor's fast
another one and short midwicket has some more work, comes up short again
absolutely perfect! It was full on off stump  and he opens the face on impact to hit the ball over and wide of mid-off. Pin point placement
140 kph, fullish on off stump as he defends quite solidly
back of a length on middle and off as he goes back and defends again
length ball on off stump as he shuffles across and defends into the on side
fullish on middle as Baz comes forward and blocks
fullish on leg stump as he stays in the crease and defends with a straight bat to mid-on
thought there was more width than there was on that length ball as he looks to cut and gets a thick inside edge down the ground
full on middle as he goes for a flick, but the ball takes the outside edge this time as he seemed to have met the ball a little too early, point loses his footing but keeps it to none
room outside off and Baz puts it away in style. Pierces the gap between point and cover as he slaps it away with a strong bottom hand
135kph, length ball on off stump as he stays back and runs the ball with an open face to point
goes uppishly towards mid-off but it bounces short. Length ball, may have come off the pitch slower as Taylor was already into his off drive on the up
short ball with tons of room outside off as Taylor leaps up and goes for a cut over third man. Gets a very big outside edge and tucks into another boundary
short and a touch too wide as he goes back and opens the face to run it down to third man. Taylor in the 90s
full and just outside off as he strides forward and strikes through the covers quite confidently
there's seven from the over without any major risk as this fullish length ball is driven through the covers
length ball on middle and it straightens a touch and Taylor has to adjust as first he was looking to tuck it away into leg and then defends
fullish and just straying down leg as he turns into the midwicket region
back of a length on and around off stump as Baz goes back and opens the face to find point
slower ball on middle and off as he drives with a straight bat down to mid-on
That's a Brendon McCullum special! Charges the medium pacer and carves him hard and flat over the covers. Hit through the line with punishing efficiency
beats him the very next ball, nice line just outside off and the length was fullish as he drew Baz into a drive, but it doesn't connect
another outside edge as this was on a good length and seams away a touch. Taylor was in his crease as he defended
the New Zealand captain is on a rampage! Gets down the track and slaps the length ball over long-off and it goes into a crowd of orange shirts, who all miss it. Monster strike.
yorker wide outside off stump as he carves it down to third man for a single. Didn't look all that comfortable fielding the ball, but he keeps it to a single
143kph, rises onto his toes as this was short and just a touch outside off, rides it down to third man
full on off stump as he drives to mid-off who is on the circle and runs through for the single

ton up for Taylor and it comes off a shot that has been immensely productive for him tonight. Off comes the helmet, out comes the tongue and Hamilton rises to it's feet as he cuts a short and wide ball over point and it goes of way faster than I can gather my thoughts on what to type. Chance-less innings and he has been incredible through the off side.
shortish and on the pads as he works it away to long leg for a single
length ball on middle as he reaches forwards to dab into the covers and calls immediately. Quick single, easily taken. Gee, these tow are quick!
bit more bounce on that, the pitch doing its bit to help India, but Baz pulled his bottom hand off and opened the face to beat point and get off strike
fullish on off as he drives with soft hands to mid-off and they scurry through for the single. India look bereft of intent here
shortish and just outside off as he stays back and opens the face to get it down to third man
touch of width outside off and that open face comes out to play again. Third man must be bushed
length and outside off as he goes back and cuts to backward point
not to short and it had only the smallest bit of width, but that has always been more than enough for Taylor in this innings. Plays the shot very late and beats backward point this time
slower through the air as he reaches forward and blocks
tossed up just outside off as he drives into the covers
absolute peach! draws him forward as he angles it in on middle and then gets it to turn right past the outside edge! Misses the off stump by a whisker
flighted on middle and leg as he turns it through midwicket to retain strike
length ball on the stumps as he defends solidly
back of a length on off stump as he opens the face and finds the gap in the covers
deep third man is a little sluggish to run across and Baz treats himself to a boundary past him. Short and just a bit wide again and punished
this time the short and wide ball is cut in front of point and along the ground, but there is a man in the deep to keep it to a couple
length ball on middle and off as he defends off the back foot
fullish on off stump as he pushes down the ground to short cover
flighted on middle and leg as he turns it away through midwicket
flighted on middle as he comes forward and blocks down the pitch
clipped away through square leg as this is short and tailing down the pads
shortish on middle and off as he dabs it to point, no single there
bit of turn as he slows it up and gives it a little more air as Taylor defends off the front foot
full, but not really flighted as he drives to long-off
131, shortish and outside off as he dabs it down to third man
chips down the track and drives into the off side. Mid-off is on the circle and by the time he got to it and threw down the stumps, Baz is well and and sneaks an overthrow
this time he gets the ball on the full and beats mid-off at his left. Excellent use of the feet as he pierces the gap and strikes a boundary that might well snuff out the contest in this chase
full toss down the leg side as Baz looks to picked it away through long leg, misses
strides down the track and even if he drags the ball short, he is in such a good position to pull the ball and the man in the deep misfields horribly at square leg

three men circle this skier and Rayudu had it in his hand, when Jaddu bumps into him and the ball slips out! Did not time this at all as this went straight up. Jaddu was at mid-on and he runs rushes forward to catch it, but Rayudu also came into the picture and that was a poor drop
back of a length on and around off stump as he gets in line and defends
142 kph, how emphatic is that?! Length ball just outside off as Baz slaps it over long-off and seals this series in a blaze of glory!
